I don't buy that the President was unaware of phone taps used on world leaders. Nobody tells him about every low or mid level person being tapped, because the list is just too long. But Angela Merkel's phone gets tapped and nobody says anything to him? Bullshit.Even if he didn't know, this disclosure serves no real purpose and is just a naked play at damage control by the White House. The NSA should be up to their eyeballs in investigations (the real kind, no rubber stamp committees), and the President should be taking heat for letting this kind of thing happen. If he didn't directly know about a small number of high profile taps, he sure as hell knew that there was illegal mass surveillance going on. No excuses, no lessening of guilt. He is an overseer of these programs, and shares responsibility for their work output.
